text.tspan: Note: The RS-422 signals are brought out to the pan/tilt side of
the connector in case somebody eventually needs to use RS-422.
RS-422 has a longer maximum cable length before signal quality
degrades enough to cause communication errors. The pan/tilt has
to be opened up and changed to RS-422 communication mode,
and a USB-to-RS-422 cable would need to be ordered and made
QPT-20 pan/tilt USB serial communication pinouts
